<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4832/76.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Special Commissioner <persName type="from">Buchanan</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Willemstadt</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-12-31"><hi rend="italic">December 31,
                                    1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Buchanan says that, accompanied by the Brazilian minister, he called
                            upon the Venezuelan minister for foreign affairs, to whom he presented a
                            copy of his commission, and also delivered to him the communication
                            addressed to him by Secretary Root. Mr. Buchanan adds that the
                            conferences were expected to begin on the following day.</p>
                    </div>
